# reducer code goes into SET_OPERATION_REDUCER without function headers

When using the `SET_OPERATION_REDUCER` MCP action, you provide only the reducer body — no function declaration, no parameter list. The framework wraps the code with the correct signature (receiving `state` and `action`).

```typescript
// ✅ What you provide to SET_OPERATION_REDUCER
state.items.push({
  id: action.input.id,
  name: action.input.name,
});

// ❌ Don't include the function wrapper
function reducer(state, action) {
  state.items.push({ ... });
}
```

Since [[external imports go in src reducer files not in SET_OPERATION_REDUCER]], the reducer code sent via MCP should contain no import statements either.

